  "text": "The LLVM optimization pass pipeline lifecycle is orchestrated through several key components:\n\n1. **PassBuilder Class** (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h, sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): The PassBuilder class is the central orchestrator for constructing optimization pipelines. It provides methods like `buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline(OptimizationLevel)` which corresponds to the O2 optimization level, `buildLTODefaultPipeline()`, and `buildO0DefaultPipeline()`. These methods are defined in PassBuilder.h (line 258-314) and implemented in PassBuilder.cpp.\n\n2. **PassManager Template Class** (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h, sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): The core pass execution engine is the PassManager template (lines 159-226), which is a CRTP-based template class taking IRUnitT as its primary parameter. Specializations include ModulePassManager and FunctionPassManager. The PassManager::run() method (line 190-191) executes all passes in sequence over the IR unit, managing analysis invalidation through PreservedAnalyses.\n\n3. **PassBuilderPipelines Implementation** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp, sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): This file contains the implementation of `PassBuilderPipelines` which assembles the default module and function simplification pipelines. It includes hundreds of pass headers and orchestrates their composition into the O0, O1, O2, O3, LTO, and ThinLTO pipelines based on optimization levels.\n\n4. **PassRegistry.def** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def, sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): This file serves as the pass registration database. It uses preprocessor macros like MODULE_PASS, FUNCTION_PASS, CGSCC_PASS, and LOOP_PASS to register all standard passes with their text names. For example, DSEPass is registered as: `FUNCTION_PASS(\"dse\", DSEPass())`\n\n5. **DeadStoreElimination (DSE) Pass** (llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.h and .cpp, sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d): A concrete example of a FunctionPass. The DSEPass class (defined in DeadStoreElimination.h line 28-31) inherits from PassInfoMixin and implements the run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM) method. The implementation uses MemorySSA analysis to identify and eliminate redundant stores. This pass is registered in PassRegistry.def and can be added to pipelines via PassBuilder.\n\nThe execution flow is: PassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() → assembles passes via PassRegistry.def registrations → passes are added to PassManager instances → PassManager::run() executes each pass in sequence with analysis invalidation tracking."
}

